		<div>haha   <br />
<br />
 Mind Crash was suggested by players on one of these types of threads and was implemented.<br />
<br />
<br />
What i'd like to see....<br />
<br />
Spells.<br />
1) Directional Shadowstep<br />
- it's an upgrade, so don't screw with it and make it long recast and stuff. no through the wall crap or anything expected.. just a great escape/travel spell we should have always had.<br />
<br />
2) Snare upgrade, <br />
- less resistable and longer duration  - I don't care if it's AoE, or single.<br />
<br />
3) Harvest upgrade.<br />
- aa or spell.. <br />
<br />
4) Reverse Coth would be nice.<br />
- target player and teleport to them.<br />
<br />
5) Disintegrate Upgrade ( lvl increase )<br />
<br />
6) Dot Absorbtion shield.<br />
<br />
7) Reflect line upgrade .. actually making it useful.. was a great idea .. just not enough.<br />
<br />
8) Huge Ether Skin upgrade.<br />
- most trash hits harder with one swing then this protects us for...it use to be a great line to absorb enough to get a root, or get abscond off .. now it's barely enough to realize you're about to die. I don't care if mana regen on it increases much .. but the amount it absorbs should be 3+ times what it is.<br />
<br />
9) Hasbeen<br />
- this spell summons a random warrior to your side to tank a mob and out dps you at the same time.<br />
<br />
AA's - <br />
1) Aggro reduction over-time ability.<br />
<br />
2) FD upgrade... less mana use or no increased mana use to get the benefit.<br />
<br />
3) Mind Crash upgrade - more aggro reduction.<br />
<br />
4) army of xzul - 3 ranks - each gives an additional sword.<br />
<br />
5) Unleached Destruction <br />
- passive<br />
- when a wizard dies with more then 85 percent of their mana unused - they have a chance to DD the target that killed them - 3 ranks (3/6/9).. each rank increases the chance ( 25/50/75) and also increases the DD damage ( 10k/20k/30k ) - resistable, magic based, can't be focused.<br />
<br />
6) moral booster - jester type avatar that continuously lies to all wizards in range - tells him how great their dps is. Randomly flips off rogues.</div>
	</td>
